UPDATE JULY 23 2019
Since June 26 it's been a battle to get a set of retainers that fit. Today, July 23rd was suppose to be the day I get a replacement but lo and behold, they're not ready. 8 weeks after getting the initial impression done for my first set, and 3 weeks after the second impression and I still do not have retainers that fit. Save yourself the trouble and go to a private office. Bright Now is the worst franchise I've ever had the mispleasure of dealing with.

This review is going to be all over the place, as I've two years of complaints.

Bright Now Dental was okay for a while. Until I became aware that their Orthodontal staff is overworked and spread much too thin. They are visibly tired and this affects their work severely. I expect a dentist to be just as excited about getting back to a healthier smile as I am. I always feel rushed when I go in there and I feel like a stranger almost every time. In the 2 + years that I've been going, my general dentist and orthodontist have changed 3 times EACH. My most recent visit I dealt with a Dr. Franco and I did not like her one bit. She was cold and offered no insight to what I can do to improve my oral hygiene. She asked me once if I had any concerns, but did not seem too interested whether or not I actually had any. On my xray, there is visible bone loss on my upper right side that she never addressed or mentioned. And my lower gumline is in desperate need of attention due to severe gum recession from braces and years of crowding. BUT THIS WAS NEVER MENTIONED. After she cleaned my teeth, she walked off without thanking me for coming in and asking me if I had any questions. Every dentist I've ever been too ALWAYS thanks the patient after they are done treatment and ask if they need anything else. If Franco's your dentist, or you're thinking about making her your's, I would reconsider.
Additionally, I've had 2 appointments in the last year cancelled with no notice from the dental staff. I've shown up for my appointment only to be told the person in charge of the instruments had an emergency and another, more recent appointment on June 8, where I showed up 10 minutes before my time, only to be met with locked doors and no staff. They claimed to have called me and left several voice mails, but I never recieved a call from them. I told the receptionist, Jenna I think was her name, that I'm fed up with the service I have been recieving from their clinic and that I'll be finding a new one. She said, "That's fine" This is a very good way to run a business. Tell your customers that it's fine if they take their business elsewhere and don't address the problems at hand.
During my last appointment, a man was in the waiting room filling out paperwork to be seen. I imagine he was on a lunch break, as he was smartly dressed. He finished his stack of paperwork and took it to Jenna, (I think that was her name. She's new to me.) the receptionist, only to be told he had MORE to fill out. He reacted very aggressively, swearing and being generally unkind. He then left, only for the receptionists and 1 other waiting room patient to begin bad mouthing him. I don't care how rude someone is to you, you do not talk ill of a patient in front of other patients. It's grossly unprofessional. This office, in Escondido Promenade is in need of some serious customer service training and they need to realize that we are people, not dollar signs.< /Review>

< review>
I am not knowledgeable of the many cell phone plans in the industry.

In error, I went to the Verizon Wireless retailer LA11D Sylmar, 13756 Foothill Boulevard, Sylmar, California, 91342.

As I prepared to travel outside of this country, I wanted to add money and extend the time of my prepaid plan so that the cellphone would not self-cancel the $90 on the account as I traveled outside the US.

I told the personnel in the Verizon Retail Center exactly what I wanted to do, they took the money, completed a transaction --

And the cellphone went dead.  I attempted to make a call.  No service.

"Maybe you can't get service in here," the manager told me.

I walked outside, attempted a call.  Dead cell phone.

I returned to the counter, asked the manager what had gone wrong.

Then the personnel discovered my cell phone operated on an AT&T prepaid plan.  Yes, incorrect company.  Incorrect retail center.

Yet they had taken my money and added the money to account that did not exist.

No account?  I asked the personnel to cancel the transaction and reset my dead cell phone.

"We didn't do anything to your cell phone."

"The phone functioned before I came in here."

"We don't know that."

I asked the store manager his name, Jhovany, he told me.  I asked for his card, he flipped a store card in my direction.  That ended the transaction.  The card he gave me did not have a name.

The name Jhovany Garcia-Chavez appears on the Sale Invoice print-out.

AT&T restored my cell phone service.  And adjusted the pre-paid plan to extend far beyond my return time to the US.

I will not return to that Retail Center.  I will tell others to avoid that Retail Center and Jhovany Garcia-Chavez. And this account will appear on the Google review for that Retail Center.

To others who read this review:  AT&T is very competent and courteous.< /review>

< review>
I was hesitant to shop for an engagement ring online, but Yadav came through 100%! I worked w/Ellie initially via the chat function, who offered me a discount and helped to facilitate payment, which was super easy. In terms of the overall experience, I preferred picking up the phone and speaking with someone, as I felt the response time, information gathering and promised production deadlines via the chat/e-mail function post purchase were a little slow, which was frustrating and disappointing.

I was super fortunate that Susan answered the phone that day I called the store post purchase. She was AMAZING at helping me choose the right setting and with customizing it. She was super friendly, patient detailed orientated, professional and was always thinking two steps ahead. She always kept her word, whether that was to call/email me back or fill me in on something. The experience would not have been the same w/o Susan! She went above and beyond and so knowledgeable! She put my mind at ease.

Nan was also great in the payment process!

The turnaround time was great. Two weeks for custom made and shipping was super quick - 1 day FedEx and the box was nice and discreet!

The ring itself is GORGEOUS! The detail and high level quality is unmatched and I found the price for the diamond I got was a steal! Definitely would recommend YADAV to others!<//review>

But all the local brick and mortar jewelry stores were just outrageous in the prices they quoted me.¬† The entire process,¬† start to finish could not have gone any smoother- I spoke primarily with Ellie and she was so patient and calm with all my dozens of questions. I purchased my center stone first but wanted to see it in person to confirm it was a keeper. Then they paid for me to ship it back to them and we started the custom design process.¬† I gave them a LOT of clear cut details and images to go on, but the end product is literally flawless and EXACTLY what I envisioned. Every detail from the right "tone" of rose gold, (I like more pink and less coppery) to the size of all the acccessory stones, to the "low profile" basket setting which was very important to me.¬† End result = 1.75 carat center oval stone (E color, VS1 clarity) set very low on a basket setting with a 1/2 pave band (2 mm wide) and a dainty hidden halo. Wedding band is 6 bezel set diamonds (0.5 carat total weight) on a 3mm rose gold band. Because the main ring is set so low, the wedding band cannot sit flush against it so they designed it in an "interrupted " fashion, meaning there is actually a gap in the wedding band to give it the illusion of sitting flush. I chose to solder the 2 rings together for this reason, so the wedding band would not spin and show the gap. It's like they read my mind and the best part is I expressed wanting it done in time for a trip to Turks and Caicos and they somehow managed to build this ring from scratch and have it in my hands in 7 days flat! It is stunning and I am so happy with it, 10/10 for Yadav!<//Review><Pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNDLd9MF1vMjXl1s25OjC87FRH4G9kzeL7sNBSP=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNvo1AnS_bekLoymW0f8jF86QhfIZ67BArghtW6=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipP-DPMsX_80o0agv61213y1dHAncziAihKPyyzU=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOVbYtDGH69NBSpXxymW0zlif-srQp1A1bMMhvl=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//Pictures>< Response>

I bought my now fiance's engagement ring at the beginning of the year.

I found the Yadav site easy to use. The price was excellent. The service (mostly via email, plus one phone call) has been excellent as well.

After selecting the stone and ring combo, there was a notice on the site letting me know that it would take a few extra days since the stone had to be mounted. It took about 10 days to arrive, which seemed fairly quick to me.

I had to send the ring back to take it down a half a size. That process was pretty seamless and they paid for the shipping.

As far as the ring is concerned, my fiance LOVES it. She has received more compliments on it than I can count. I'm not much for jewelry myself, but I find myself staring at the stone. It's mesmerizing.

Overall, I think this purchase went as well as it could have. I don't regret not buying the ring locally. I got a great deal and there were no hiccups.

I 100% recommend this company.</text>

< review>
I am writing this review largely in part due to the amazing customer service I received from Nan. I have never in my life met a customer service associate who is more responsive and helpful than her. Thank you Nan, you are amazing!

Unfortunately, there were a few hiccups when it came to my ring. My fianc√© found Yadav through Rare Carat. Don't get me wrong, I absolutely love my ring. However, there were a couple flaws which should not have passed their quality control when it comes to an engagement ring. I had to send my ring back in for a resize as it was too big. The process to ship the ring back was extremely easy (thanks to Nan) and I was able to receive it back in a week. But when I got it back, I realized that it was crooked and there were two gaps in the ring (as pictured). I had taken a couple pictures before sending it back as well which I was able to show as proof that the gaps happened after the resizing. Thankfully, Yadav agreed to take the ring back and fix the gaps which I was very grateful for, though I was now anxious I would have to ship my ring back a second time and be apart from it for another week. When I got my ring back for the final time (two pictures against white marbled background), the gap on the part of the band with the row of diamonds had been fixed (yay!) But the gap in the middle still remains.

I love my ring so much and don't want to part with it anymore, so I don't mind the gap too much as it is pretty hard to see unless you're extremely close and scrutinizing. I would just think, for such an expensive ring with such a beautiful diamond, you'd hope the quality is 100%.

All in all, amazing customer service but 1 star off for the quality control.< /review>

<Name>Alexandria Cell<//Name>< Review>
I am STUNNED by Yadav's service. I'd been in awe looking at their diamonds online for awhile now, which are consistently priced very competitively, and I found a pair of 3/4 total carat weight diamond studs for the same cost as the best-priced 1/2 carat studs from anywhere else (and Yadav's were better quality, too!) in December. After wearing them for 3 months straight (true everyday earrings!), the back of one of the earrings fell out when I was in public, and I couldn't find it. At 4:50pm today (Friday) I called to ask if I could come in to get a replacement backing (hoping it would only cost $100-200), and the very nice woman on the phone said they would have availability for me to come in today! When I arrived an employee was very nice and found a backing that matched my earring. Then she said I was good to go? And that the replacement backing is complimentary as part of their service guarantee?! As someone with a tendency to lose things, my mind is blown! We didn't pay up for the service guarantee, and I didn't even have to provide any proof of purchase. I understand how valuable service is, but you're not even paying up for the service -- it's almost the opposite! I fully recommend Yadav to the internet, just as I have for a friend who got their wedding rings and engagement ring at Yadav a couple months ago!

TL;DR: best prices and service in the jewelry industry<//Review>

<Review>My husband and I decided that we would celebrate our ten year anniversary by upgrading my engagement ring with a diamond. I had helped choose the original centerstone a decade ago, which was an inexpensive (i.e. $65) light green prasiolite in a chunky size. Yadav's excellent sales reps helped us choose the most beautiful diamond in exactly the dimensions and characteristics we were hoping for to fit my current setting. Yadav did a perfect job with the prong metal work and returned my upgraded ring plus my original stone in a gorgeous box, complete with paperwork. <date>1610498108887</date>< Rate>

<review>I ordered an engagement diamond through this company after seeing the one I liked on Rarecarat and had it shipped to me. Normally I make large purchases like this in person, especially if it was jewelry, so that I can inspect it and don't have to worry about shipping. Luckily, they had detailed descriptions, photos, and 360 video of the diamond itself so I felt confident enough to make the purchase.

Shipping was very very secure as the diamond was wonderfully packaged in its own little metal capsule, in a weighty box, inside shipping bag, inside a medium box, then AGAIN inside a large shipping box. It had multiple layers of protection and there was no way of telling it was a multi thousand dollar diamond inside. It also required signature on delivery.

The customer service was quick to respond if I wanted a refund, exchange, or shipping updates. The only downside was that the shipping took about two weeks.

Fiance absolutely loves the diamond and gets compliments on it all the time. Keep in mind this was a lab grown, 1,63, ideal cut, oval, vvs2, colorless, all for $4300. Robins Brothers wanted $10,000 for an equivalent lab grown diamond.

That is the last taboo, not related to this company. We were skeptical about getting a lab grown and the comments that may come along with it so we went to check out both lab grown and mined diamonds in person. The salesperson laid 3 lab grown and 3 mined in front of us to let us decide which one is which. After feeling confident on our choices we were completely wrong. There is no way to tell by eye the difference between lab grown and mined unless youre an absolute expert on it. So fellas, you can go up in size and quality by going this route.< /review>< pictures>

Yadav was on the lower-end price-wise but their quality and service surpasses every other online vendor I've dealt with. <review>I recently got an engagement ring from Yadav and it was a really great online experience.  I started looking early in the year and COVID hit.  I mentioned the time frame I was looking and felt no "salesman" like pressure from them.  Always a plus to not feel rushed or forced.

<Rate>5< /Rate>< review>
I ordered an engagement ring from Yadav and had an excellent experience.  I ordered a 2.22 carat stone with a platinum setting.  Based on my extensive research of the all of the online jewelers, such as James Allen and Blue Nile, I felt Yadav offered a much larger and attractive selection of settings. I was nervous making such a large purchase online, but it all worked out great in the end.  Upon receiving the ring, I took it to a local jeweler to verify it was authentic.  It was the real deal and the jeweler commented on the excellent quality of main stone.  I missed the mark on the ring size on the initial order and we had to send it back a few times to get the size perfect.  Yadav made it easy with prepaid FedEx shipping labels.  They were always gracious about it and never make us feel like it was an inconvenience.  Overall, I feel like we received an excellent price and a quality engagement ring.  In the big picture the temporary sizing issues was well worth the money I saved versus going to a local big named jewelry store.  I can‚Äôt imagine what a local jewelry store would have charged me for a similar ring, but suspect at least 40% more based upon my research.< /review>

<userid>100866558558407039137</userid>< name>
Scarlet Chen</name>
< date>
1565930738782<//date>
< Rating>
4< /Rating>
< Text>
Yadav is a honest and responsive business with good diamond and attitude but bad contractor for their rings. Me and my bf are planning to get engaged so I was looking for an engagement diamond online and found one that I like offered by Yadav. A bit on online diamonds: nowadays there's a ton of online diamond website, I think it's basically worth it to get diamonds online cuz the mark-up in physical shops are crazy, but since online diamond stores don't profit that much from their diamonds they may try to make that up by selling slightly over-priced settings. And even among online stores some are more expensive than others, like I think brilliant earth is more expensive than others; the same diamond may get listed on different store's website, like the one I picked was on Yadav and another online store called `with clarity', but Yadav's price is better, so I went with Yadav. Another funny thing is that although Yadav's diamond is cheaper than the other store, the setting is cheaper on the other store's website than Yadav's, so overall the market seems to be quite efficient. So I think the best strategy is to buy the diamond you like from the cheapest website online, and find a local physical jewelry shop to buy a setting. The mistake I made was buying a setting with Yadav: 1) it's expensive: $550 for 18k white gold solitaire setting 2) the first time they gave me a ring of the wrong size and wrong material (14 k instead of 18k) and 3) the second time they did ship me the ring size and material ring, but the diamond is clearly not set in the dead-center of the ring, and the 4 prongs of the ring were not equally spaced, so the ring looked very ugly. But they were super responsive and responsible during the whole process- they always reply email the next day, and they did stand up to what they promised - free return within 30 days with no question asked, and they gave me pre-paid shipping label with insurance on the shipping. I think what happened is that their business model is just to cut cost as much as possible so that they can earn money even when selling diamond at low margin, so they basically find the cheapest contractor out there to make their rings, which means their rings are poor-quality. So I would suggest buying diamond from them but not the ring, and find local jewelry shop to get a ring setting and set the diamond.<//Text>

<date>1548965340318< /date><rate>5< /rate><text>The ring was beautiful and the diamond is great, but there is fire scale/discoloration on the ring after only 5 months. The ring was 18K yellow gold, and the soldered joints are turning a rose gold color. We confirmed with a local jeweler that the ring should not be turning this color; it should've been fused, not soldered. I expressed my disappointment with Yadav, and their response was that the discoloration was due to normal wear and tear (in 5 months!), and offered to polish the ring if we paid $70 to ship it back to them. I replied that the discoloration was not due to normal wear and tear but was in fact due to poor craftsmanship. That email was sent on November 16th, and I have not received a reply, hence this review.

UPDATE 1: I have head back from the owner; they agreed to pay to ship the ring back and check it out, so they have worked to rectify the situation. As such, I have adjusted my rating to 3 stars, and we'll see how the situation gets solved ultimately.

I believe they had a knew one built (although that was never made clear to me) and shipped it back. I believe the process took about 3 weeks.

<user_name>Joe Charles<//user_name><time>1523370930712< /time><rating>5<//rating><text>Yadav was recommended to me by a friend who likes to do meticulous research on things before buying them. I wasn't nervous about buying a diamond online necessarily, but I was unsure of how it would work, since the last time I bought a diamond, I went from store to store looking at loose diamonds until I found the right one.

I called Yadav and they assured me on the phone that they would overnight the diamond, and if it wasn't to my liking, I could just send it back, on their dime. What did I have to lose?

Yadav's website made it very easy to search through many different diamonds at once. You can enter in various search criteria in terms of cost, quality, etc., and then you can look at each actual diamond and its associated GIA report (if applicable). Most came with a full 360-view video, and I found this to be very easy to see any defect/inclusions at different angles.

Once I selected a diamond, it was overnighted to me, double-boxed in a standard large UPS priority box, with no obvious signage on the outside that the box contained anything of significant value. The return address did not even mention that it came from a jewelry store.

In my case, the diamond was exactly what was displayed online, down to every last detail. There were no unexpected surprises. What I saw was what I got, and it was stunning!

Fantastic quality at an amazing price. I am 100% satisfied, and would recommend Yadav to anyone looking for a diamond.< /text><Pics>None< /Pics><resp>None</resp>< gmapID>
